Pseudocode01

Specs -

To write a criteria to automatically generate a short login name from the first name and fathers name which are taken in to the database from a user, the criteria can use grand fathers name which also will be taken from the user in two database in the users entity.

Pseudo code -

- prompt the user to input in a form  the first name, fathers name and grand fathers name in a label
- the user inputs the first name, fathers name and grand fathers name into a text box and clicks a button
- store the user's input (first_name, fathers_name and g_fathers_name) into the sql table fields
- take the record of the first_name and append the first character of fathers_name in to it
- check if it is not available in the login filed record of the database if so put that in the login field
- if it is already taken additionally append the first character of the grand fathers name in to it 
- check if it is not available in the login filed record of the database if so put that in the login field
- if it is already taken additionally append the university_id in to it and put it the loin filed in the database 
- display the final user Log in name as a report in addition to users registration success information report 

